commitResults.messageBody:
Implemented a menu bar following https://electronjs.org/docs/api/menu.
Successfully run on 'npm start' however, compiling to a desktop app
causes error.

As per the last commit, the bug related to the building of the
application (specifically on MacOS) has been fixed. The app now
functions with a working menu-bar and shortcuts (tested on Mac).
Removed Text-To-Speech component as it was unecessary.

Commented out the release code and placed a TODO comment as a reminder
to remove prior to releasing as referenced in #49.

Initially the click event was always registered by the entire row. As
such even clicking a button on the particular row had caused the page to
load a new routerlink and carry out the button's task as well. Hence
when a click is detected on a button on the row, the event is not
propogated to the row itself. Thus only carrying out the task of the
button.

Accidental change in the file (removed a space). Reverted so that it
does not appear as a changed file in the PR.

* Search bar widths increased

Search Bar Widths for each phase has been increased to fill the size of
the grid they are positioned in. Mainly linked each mat-form-field to a
css class and increased the widths through the css implementation.

Refer to  #54

* Moved the CSS Style Class to Global CSS file.

Moved the class that expands the search-bar's length to the global
styles.css to reduce repeated code.

* Removed Erroneous Code

Accidental Code that wasn't initially removed is now deleted.

commitResults.messageTitle: Replaced Pop-up dialog with Material Dialog.
commitResults.messageBody:
As per #46, replaced the pop-up with the material version that lies
within the application rather than opening a new window that causes
modality issues.

commitResults.messageTitle: Added Propoagtion stop for Delete Button Phase 1
commitResults.messageBody:
The delete button in the row of the table in Phase 1 was lacking the
stopPropogation directive that caused the issue to open, it has now been
added.

commitResults.messageTitle: Minor UI Tweak Duplicated Issues -> Duplicates
commitResults.messageBody:
A minor UI Tweak that changes the header of the tables in Phase 2 from
"Duplicated Issues" to Duplicates. Refer to #52.

The profiles select menu now works, we can now select a relevant profile
and phase in the dropdown menu and autofill the user authentication
data.
Added some commenting and code style fixes (Line length limit adherence.)

Currently the Reading From JSON components and parsing of data to the
relevant fields is complete.

Next: Create a Dialog informing the user of any errors in their json
file.

commitResults.messageTitle: Working profiles.json reading and data validation.
commitResults.messageBody:
The app is now able to read from an internal profiles.json during the
dev phase as well as an external profiles.json within the same directory
as the app in production. This commit also includes some level of data
validation to ensure that the json file is setup correctly.
Implemented some codestyle changes and code commenting.
Added some comments to the code for clarity.

commitResults.messageTitle: Commented Out Auto-Dev tool Open Line
commitResults.messageBody:
Left the line commented out so that it can be re-used later in the dev
phase. Reference to #74

A built in function now verifies that the app is in DevMode prior to
inserting the DevTools option. Now, prior to release, we need to
uncomment the enableProdMode() function so that Electron knows not to
add the DevToolsMenu. Reference with #75
Correctly Pulled roles csv data from correct repo. Saving changes.

* Duplicate Dropdown Text Fix

Previously the duplicate items that have long names would not display
the 'A duplicated issue' tag [They would be outside the box]. Fixed the
issue with some styling and ngStyle where the width restriction only
activates if the issue is a duplicate one.

* Selective ToolTips

Tooltips appear in the duplicates dropdown menu only when the text has
been truncated or obscured by the (Duplicate Issue) postfix.

* Rename Function

Renaming of function to increase consistency with its return value and
what the return signifies.

* Minor Tweaks

Changed the following
    -   Div under mat option now follows a style class instead of id
    -   Threshold to display non-duplicate tooltip
    -   CSS ID to Class

* Code style Fixes

Changes to the code style to improve clarity and adhere to the 80
character code length limit.

* Further Codestyle Fixes

Manual Parsing is working but need to search for an existing library.
Saving state.

Current version of csv import and parsing works completely, now working
on reducing verbosity and improving coding standard.
Fixed an error that appears in the console.

commitResults.messageTitle: Code cleanup and Working CSV Import
commitResults.messageBody:
CSV Import is fully working. This commit mainly does some code cleanup
and reduction in verbosity.

A single CSV file is now able to construct the Datafile in a JSON format
for the application.

commitResults.messageTitle: Admin No Longer Requires a Team
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously the admin had to be assigned to a team to log in. That
requirement has been removed.

commitResults.messageTitle: README.md Updated to Reflect use of data.csv

commitResults.messageBody:
By using IPC to communicate the application directory during dev mode
and regex to isolate the .app / .exe during production mode there will
be no need to differentiate between Dev and Prod mode to source for
profiles.json.
Proceeding with some code cleanup.

commitResults.messageTitle: BugReportingRepository will be automatically created for Students (#189)
commitResults.messageBody:
* BugReport Repo will be automatically created.

The BugReporting Phase Repository will be automatically created and
setup if it is missing during the initial log-in. Since the users are
required to have this repo for the PE.

* Streamline Repo Creation Process

Repository Initialization works only for the Bug Reporting Phase and
only for Students in that phase. (So Tutors/Admins will not have a
random repository created in their account). Error messages have been
put in place to identify any potential faliures.

repository was detected to be unavailable but it has now been narrowed
